As schools remain closed due to the outbreak of coronavirus, the Borno State government has kicked off home learning programme via its radio and television for senior secondary schools (SS3) students. The commissioner for Education, Hon. Bello Ayuba, disclosed this at the weekend in Maiduguri, the state capital. Ayuba, said the decision was taken after a meeting with the permanent secretary, Alhaji  Ali Kaka, the ministerial secretary,  Alhaji Sadiq Kadafur and a host of other directors from the ministry. “We were at  the office of the Perm secretary Alhaji Ali Kaka  to flag off the learning at home programme for SSS III Students against the stay at home COVID – 19 pandemic. “The programmes comprise seventy percent of the subjects taught at the senior school levels. Competent teachers are chosen from few schools to run the programme at 45 minutes per lesson. “The media houses to air the lessons are: NTA, BRTV, DANDAL KURA, Peace FM and other social media platforms such as Instagram, twitter, Facebook, WhatsApp and so on,” Ayuba said.